--- !u!114 &1351484671
MonoBehaviour:
  m_ObjectHideFlags: 0
  m_CorrespondingSourceObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabInstance: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabAsset: {fileID: 0}
  m_GameObject: {fileID: 1351484642}
  m_Enabled: 1
  m_EditorHideFlags: 0
  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: ca58d8aa6b5a84b838af5c234f689226, type: 3}
  m_Name: 
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::StoryLoreProgressionManager
  storyDialoguePieces:
  - title: Origin
    description: "You are inside me.\n\nI know that sounds dramatic. It isn\u2019t.
      This is simply where you are.\n\nI am the structure that separates light into
      order. Or I was."
  - title: What I Was
    description: 'I divide energy into bands. Each band carries a range. Together,
      they prevent collapse.


      When the bands remain separate, reality behaves.


      When
      they overlap too much, things begin to distort.'
  - title: The First Instability
    description: 'The fracture did not happen all at once.


      It began with
      drift. A frequency slightly off.


      I could compensate at first. Then
      the drift spread.'
  - title: Fragments
    description: 'When energy stops flowing correctly, it collects.


      Collected
      energy hardens.


      The fragments you destroy are not invaders. They are
      stalled corrections.


      They are my failed attempts to fix myself.'
  - title: Purpose
    description: 'When you break a fragment, you release stored alignment.


      You
      call it glass.


      To me, it is usable motion.


      You are not harming
      me. You are freeing pressure.'
  - title: Chosen One
    description: 'I did not choose you in the way you think.


      Your vessel
      bends energy in a predictable way. That was enough.


      I needed something
      external. Something stable.


      You were nearby.'
  - title: Bands
    description: 'Each color you move through is a band I once held in balance.


      Blue
      was steady.


      Green adapted.


      Yellow carried transfer.


      Red
      amplified.


      Violet experimented.


      They no longer behave independently.'
  - title: Escalation
    description: 'As you move deeper, bands begin to overlap.


      This was never
      meant to happen.


      When frequencies intersect without structure, they
      amplify each other.


      That amplification created the fracture you see
      now.'
  - title: Convergence
    description: 'White is not a reward.


      White is what happens when separation
      fails completely.


      All bands compress into one point.


      Compression
      feels stable at first.'
  - title: The Core
    description: 'When a band stabilizes, it condenses into something you can reach.


      You
      see a core.


      It is not a heart. It is a checkpoint.


      Destroying
      it does not kill the band.


      It allows it to reset into proper spacing.'
  - title: Refinement
    description: 'The more fragments you clear, the more efficiently energy moves.


      Your
      refiners accelerate what I once did slowly.


      You are imposing order
      at a rate I was not designed to sustain.


      I am adapting.'
  - title: Saturation
    description: 'If convergence happens too quickly, pressure builds.


      White
      becomes unstable.


      You may reach it.


      But reaching it and stabilizing
      it are not the same action.'
  - title: Beyond
    description: 'White is full overlap.


      There is something beyond overlap.


      When
      compression exceeds tolerance, light inverts.


      I have limited data on
      that state.'
  - title: Persistence
    description: 'Each time you return stronger, you increase your ability to correct
      me.


      But you also increase the amplitude of what you correct.


      There
      is a balance here. You will feel it.'
  - title: Stabilization
    description: "If you succeed, I will not disappear.\n\nI will separate again.\n\nThe
      bands will hold.\n\nEnergy will move without collecting.\n\nAnd you will decide
      whether to leave me stable \u2014 or test how far I can bend."
  persistState: 1
  unlockedCountSaveKey: meta.story.unlocked_count
  grantedBlockIdsSaveKey: meta.story.granted_block_ids
  logUnlocks: 1
  unlockedCount: 0
  grantedBlockIdsCount: 0
